node.text:
Some need drugs to get high.  I simply need to listen to music.

It taps into every aspect of my soul.

The math side
The reflection side
The imagination side

Songs take me to many places.  It helps me travel.

Listening to Bronski beat “small town boy” takes me back to Germany at the refugee camp.

Listening to Foreigner “I want to know what love is” takes me back to the Army at Fort Campbell, Kentucky.

Listening to Sting “Fields of Gold” takes me back to Grad Night at magic mountain waiting in line for log jammer.

Listening to Jacques Brel “ne me quitte pas” takes me back to driving towards bandar Pahlavi in Iran with my family.

Listening to Kenny Rogers “Lady” takes me back to my wedding.

Listening to Celly Cel “It’s going down tonight” takes me back to Palm Springs with my friends.

Listening to David Guetta “The world is mine” takes me back to running my sales office in Granada Hills & Northridge.

Music soothes my soul.

I thank God for the ability to listen to great music.

I feel like I’m the luckiest man alive... even on days when nothing goes right!

Love ya!

node.text: Here’s why👇🏽

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Patrick Bet-David in Dallas, Texas with @aguilarsocial, and @ellsworth.thomas. May be an image of 3 people, people sitting, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
Working on 7 major project at the same time.

One is more exciting than the other.

Stay tuned!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Patrick Bet-David in Boca Raton, Florida. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Patrick Bet-David @patrickbetdavid We are the luckiest generation alive. Don't let the media convince you that it's the worst. It's utter non sense and absolutely disgusting. What's needed is gratitude. What's needed is love. What's needed is perspective. What's needed is the ability to question NON SENSE!'.

node.text:
Don’t buy the BS.

Every day I run into amazing people.

Every day people validate why the future looks bright.

Every day I see examples of great men and women.

Every day I see strangers who who help other strangers without caring about the politics, color of their skin or religion.

It makes no difference to me whether you’re white, black, latino, asian, educated, not educated, tall, short, married, single, republican, democrat, independent or someone who could care less for politics.

But if you’re a bully, a manipulator, a divider, a person who plays games who gets joy from destroying a beautiful family, a great company or country, you won’t win in the end.

History doesn’t them.

Future looks bright!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Patrick Bet-David in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. May be an image of 3 people and text that says 'Patrick Bet-David on Google Suggest edits more Patrick Bet-David American actor Overview Interviews Books Videos Movies P ENTRE AMAN Born: October 18, 1978 (age 42 years), Tehran, Iran'.

node.text:
Apparently Google thinks I’m an American actor.

I’m not sure whether they’re forecasting or know something I don’t know.

I’ll take it as a compliment. 😂

node.text: Caption 👇🏽

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Patrick Bet-David on July 03, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'Patrick Bet-David @patrickbetdavid Underachievers think they're working harder than they actually are. Overachievers think they're not working hard enough. Underachievers think they know it all. Overachievers think they don't know it all. History favors the overachiever!'.

node.text:
The sprinkle of paranoia in overachievers is what makes them constantly improve and advance.

It’s the constant mindset of what could I have done better.

What skill do I need to learn in today’s economy? Not the skills that helped me in the 2000’s or 2010’s but what’ll be necessary between now and 2025?

This is coming from a person who was an underachiever most of his life. I know what I it to be an underachiever as well as an achiever but it’s the overachiever I’m constantly striving for.

Power to the those who strive to be overachievers.

Tag one 👇🏽
